<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3325] Compaction degrades key cache stats</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3325</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &quot;compaction_preheat_key_cache&quot; is set to true, then during compaction, it keep tracks of cached keys to to re-cache their new position.&lt;br/&gt;
It does this by calling  the following method on every key of the compacted sstable :&lt;br/&gt;
sstable.getCachedPosition(row.key)&lt;br/&gt;
which also update cache stats, thus lowering hit rate&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Below is an attached patch allowing to know if the key is cached, but without updating the stats.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
